chapter.paragraph:
Every test name starts with a verb like every other method that's primary function is an action. Every test name should refer to the primarily tested thing (Object/Method/Function/Class), the tested feature, the tested situation and the tested result in that order (This is based on
Naming standards for unit tests by Roy Osherove https://osherove.com/blog/2005/4/3/naming-standards-for-unit-tests.html
). All referred things in the method name, should be referred to, by its original name.
